verbose_text: In human bone, increased cell viability and proliferation, alkaline phosphatase activity (ALP), and the expression of osteopontin and sialoprotein XREF_BIBR Osteoblastic cells are stimulated by low intensity laser radiation to modify the production of mediators as a function of time, frequency and dose applied, mainly in laser with wavelength in the range of 635nm and 805nm XREF_BIBR.
